{"id":181,"date":"2026-05-09T10:06:47","date_gmt":"2026-05-09T10:06:47","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/how-2.codes\/?p=181"},"modified":"2026-05-09T10:06:47","modified_gmt":"2026-05-09T10:06:47","slug":"how-to-disable-onedrive-completely","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/how-2.codes\/how-to-disable-onedrive-completely\/","title":{"rendered":"How to \u201cDISABLE ONEDRIVE COMPLETELY\u201d"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\"><strong>DISABLE ONEDRIVE COMPLETELY<\/strong><br \/>\n\t\t<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">ok 1st lets completely disable via registry and whatever else. i don&#8217;t use it and don&#8217;t want it at all to be accessible<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">Understood \u2014 you want to\u00a0<strong>completely disable SMB and file sharing at the system level<\/strong>, not just stop services temporarily. Here&#8217;s a thorough approach that covers registry, services, and network stack so SMB is no longer accessible:<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-size:15pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI Emoji\">\ud83d\udd27<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\"> Disable SMB Server (LanmanServer)<br \/>\n<\/span><\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<div><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">Stop and disable the service:<br \/>\n<\/span><\/div>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">powershell<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"background: #f6f8fa\"><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">Stop-Service LanmanServer -Force<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"background: #f6f8fa\"><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">Set-Service LanmanServer -StartupType Disabled<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">Registry harddisable:<br \/>\n<\/span><\/div>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">powershell<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"background: #f6f8fa\"><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">Set-ItemProperty -Path &#8216;HKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanServer&#8217; -Name &#8216;Start&#8217; -Value 4<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-size:15pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI Emoji\">\ud83d\udd27<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\"> Disable SMB Client (LanmanWorkstation)<br \/>\n<\/span><\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<div><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">Stop and disable the service:<br \/>\n<\/span><\/div>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">powershell<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"background: #f6f8fa\"><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">Stop-Service LanmanWorkstation -Force<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"background: #f6f8fa\"><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">Set-Service LanmanWorkstation -StartupType Disabled<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">Registry harddisable:<br \/>\n<\/span><\/div>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">powershell<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"background: #f6f8fa\"><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">Set-ItemProperty -Path &#8216;HKLM:\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanWorkstation&#8217; -Name &#8216;Start&#8217; -Value 4<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-size:15pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI Emoji\">\ud83d\udd27<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\"> Disable SMB Protocol Versions<br \/>\n<\/span><\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">Windows allows you to disable SMBv1, SMBv2, SMBv3 individually:<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<div><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">Disable SMBv1:<br \/>\n<\/span><\/div>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">powershell<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"background: #f6f8fa\"><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">Set-SmbServerConfiguration -EnableSMB1Protocol $false -Force<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"background: #f6f8fa\"><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">Disable-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online -FeatureName SMB1Protocol -NoRestart<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<\/li>\n<li>\n<div><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">Disable SMBv2\/3:<br \/>\n<\/span><\/div>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">powershell<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"background: #f6f8fa\"><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">Set-SmbServerConfiguration -EnableSMB2Protocol $false -Force<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-size:15pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI Emoji\">\ud83d\udd27<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\"> Firewall Rules<br \/>\n<\/span><\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">Block inbound\/outbound SMB ports:<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">TCP 445 (SMB over TCP)<br \/>\n<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">TCP\/UDP 139 (NetBIOS Session)<br \/>\n<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">UDP 137\u2013138 (NetBIOS Name\/Datagram)<br \/>\n<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">powershell<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"background: #f6f8fa\"><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">New-NetFirewallRule -DisplayName &#8220;Block SMB Inbound&#8221; -Direction Inbound -Protocol TCP -LocalPort 445,139 -Action Block<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"background: #f6f8fa\"><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">New-NetFirewallRule -DisplayName &#8220;Block SMB Outbound&#8221; -Direction Outbound -Protocol TCP -LocalPort 445,139 -Action Block<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"background: #f6f8fa\"><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">New-NetFirewallRule -DisplayName &#8220;Block NetBIOS UDP&#8221; -Direction Inbound -Protocol UDP -LocalPort 137,138 -Action Block<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-size:15pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI Emoji\">\ud83d\udd27<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\"> Disable NetBIOS over TCP\/IP<br \/>\n<\/span><\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">Go to\u00a0<strong>Network Adapter Properties \u2192 IPv4 \u2192 Advanced \u2192 WINS tab \u2192 Disable NetBIOS over TCP\/IP<\/strong>.<br \/>\n<\/span><\/li>\n<li>\n<div><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">Or via registry (per adapter):<br \/>\n<\/span><\/div>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color:#24292e\"><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\">Key:\u00a0<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">HKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\NetBT\\Parameters\\Interfaces\\Tcpip_{GUID}<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\"><br \/>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/span><\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color:#24292e\"><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\">Value:\u00a0<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">NetbiosOptions = 2<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\">\u00a0(disable)<br \/>\n<\/span><\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-size:15pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI Emoji\">\ud83d\udd27<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\"> Verify<br \/>\n<\/span><\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">After reboot:<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color:#24292e\"><span style=\"font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">Get-SmbShare<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\">\u00a0should fail with &#8220;Server service is not started.&#8221;<br \/>\n<\/span><\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color:#24292e\"><span style=\"font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">Get-Service LanmanServer,LanmanWorkstation<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\">\u00a0should show\u00a0<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">Disabled<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\">.<br \/>\n<\/span><\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color:#24292e\"><span style=\"font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">netstat -ano | findstr 445<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\">\u00a0should return nothing.<br \/>\n<\/span><\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e\"><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI Emoji\">\u26a0\ufe0f<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\">\u00a0<strong>Note<\/strong>: Disabling SMB completely means you won&#8217;t be able to access network shares, printers, or certain Windows features (like remote admin tools). If you&#8217;re sure you don&#8217;t use any of these, this is safe.<br \/>\n<\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/previous is already done new UPDATED STEPS<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">Got it \u2014 since SMB and sharing are already disabled, the remaining piece is\u00a0<strong>locking down OneDrive<\/strong>\u00a0so it can&#8217;t sync or expose your Documents folder. Here are the main ways to fully disable OneDrive on Windows:<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-size:15pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI Emoji\">\ud83d\udd27<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\"> Disable OneDrive via Group Policy (best if available)<br \/>\n<\/span><\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color:#24292e\"><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\">Run\u00a0<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">gpedit.msc<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\">.<br \/>\n<\/span><\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color:#24292e\"><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\">Navigate to:\u00a0<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">Computer Configuration \u2192 Administrative Templates \u2192 Windows Components \u2192 OneDrive<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\"><br \/>\n\t\t\t\t<\/span><\/span><\/li>\n<li>\n<div><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">Enable\u00a0<strong>&#8220;Prevent the usage of OneDrive for file storage.&#8221;<\/strong><br \/>\n\t\t\t\t<\/span><\/div>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">This stops OneDrive from running or syncing entirely.<br \/>\n<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-size:15pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI Emoji\">\ud83d\udd27<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\"> Disable OneDrive via Registry<br \/>\n<\/span><\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">If you don&#8217;t have Group Policy (e.g., Windows Home edition):<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">powershell<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"background: #f6f8fa\"><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">New-ItemProperty -Path &#8220;HKLM:\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\OneDrive&#8221; -Name &#8220;DisableFileSync&#8221; -PropertyType DWord -Value 1 -Force<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">Reboot afterwards.<br \/>\n<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">This registry key enforces the same policy as above.<br \/>\n<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-size:15pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI Emoji\">\ud83d\udd27<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\"> Uninstall OneDrive (optional, but permanent)<br \/>\n<\/span><\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">Run in elevated PowerShell:<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">powershell<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"background: #f6f8fa\"><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">taskkill \/f \/im OneDrive.exe<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"background: #f6f8fa\"><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">%SystemRoot%\\System32\\OneDriveSetup.exe \/uninstall<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"background: #f6f8fa\"><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">%SystemRoot%\\SysWOW64\\OneDriveSetup.exe \/uninstall<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">This removes the OneDrive client.<br \/>\n<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">Your local files remain, but syncing is gone.<br \/>\n<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-size:15pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI Emoji\">\ud83d\udd27<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\"> Lock Down OneDrive Folder ACLs<br \/>\n<\/span><\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">If you want to keep OneDrive installed but block access:<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">powershell<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"background: #f6f8fa\"><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">$oneDrivePath = &#8220;$env:USERPROFILE\\OneDrive&#8221;<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"background: #f6f8fa\"><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">if (Test-Path $oneDrivePath) {    takeown \/F $oneDrivePath \/R \/D Y    icacls $oneDrivePath \/inheritance:d \/T    icacls $oneDrivePath \/remove:g Everyone \/T    icacls $oneDrivePath \/remove:g &#8220;Authenticated Users&#8221; \/T    icacls $oneDrivePath \/grant &#8220;Administrators:(F)&#8221; \/T    icacls $oneDrivePath \/grant &#8220;SYSTEM:(F)&#8221; \/T    icacls $oneDrivePath \/grant &#8220;$env:USERNAME:(F)&#8221; \/T<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"background: #f6f8fa\"><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">}<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">This ensures only you, SYSTEM, and Administrators have access.<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-size:15pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI Emoji\">\u2705<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\"> Summary<br \/>\n<\/span><\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\"><strong>Group Policy \/ Registry<\/strong>\u00a0\u2192 clean disable of OneDrive sync.<br \/>\n<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\"><strong>Uninstall<\/strong>\u00a0\u2192 removes the client completely.<br \/>\n<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\"><strong>ACL lockdown<\/strong>\u00a0\u2192 restricts access to the OneDrive folder itself.<br \/>\n<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/BLOCK ONE DRIVE REINSTALLATION<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-size:15pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI Emoji\">\ud83d\udee1<\/span><span style=\"font-family:Segoe UI\">\ufe0f Block Reinstallation<br \/>\n<\/span><\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">Since you already enabled the Group Policy\u00a0<em>Prevent the usage of OneDrive for file storage<\/em>, that will stop OneDrive from coming back. For extra assurance, set the registry key:<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Segoe UI\">powershell<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n<p style=\"background: #f6f8fa\"><span style=\"color:#24292e; font-family:Consolas; font-size:10pt\">New-ItemProperty -Path &#8220;HKLM:\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\OneDrive&#8221; -Name &#8221;<br \/>\n<\/span><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>DISABLE ONEDRIVE COMPLETELY ok 1st lets completely disable via registry and whatever else. i don&#8217;t use it and don&#8217;t want it at all to be accessible Understood \u2014 you want to\u00a0completely disable SMB and file sharing at the system level, not just stop services temporarily. Here&#8217;s a thorough approach that covers registry, services, and network [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_import_markdown_pro_load_document_selector":0,"_import_markdown_pro_submit_text_textarea":"","footnotes":""},"categories":[1],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-181","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-uncategorized"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/how-2.codes\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/181","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/how-2.codes\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/how-2.codes\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/how-2.codes\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/how-2.codes\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=181"}],"version-history":[{"count":1,"href":"https:\/\/how-2.codes\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/181\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":182,"href":"https:\/\/how-2.codes\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/181\/revisions\/182"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/how-2.codes\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=181"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/how-2.codes\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=181"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/how-2.codes\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=181"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}